OL,3,CMen jailed after head-on 90mph crash
OL,4,Cwith unmarked police car
OL,6,FMinutes later, as it was being pursued
OL,7,Fby marked police patrols, the group
OL,8,Fploughed the car, head-on, into an
OL,9,Funmarked police car on patrol on
OL,10,FHeyworth Street in Everton.
OL,12,FThe vehicle, driven by O'Connor, 37,
OL,13,Fwas said to have been travelling at up
OL,14,Fto 90mph prior to the crash.
OL,16,FO'Connor, of Anfield, Liverpool, fled
OL,17,Fthe car before being detained nearby
OL,18,Fon the pavement, while the teenager
OL,19,Fwas discovered with an injury to his
OL,20,Fleg in the front passenger seat.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
