OL,3,CMen jailed after head-on 90mph crash
OL,4,Cwith unmarked police car
OL,6,FHis counsel, Brendan Carville, told
OL,7,Fthe court: "He is not in good health.
OL,8,FWhile in prison, he has been tested
OL,9,Ffor bowel cancer. He is awaiting the
OL,10,Fresults of that.
OL,12,F"He bitterly regrets his involvement
OL,13,Fin this. He has little memory of what
OL,14,Fhappened and is lucky to be alive,
OL,15,Fgiven the crash that occurred head-on.
OL,16,FHe feels very stupid to be involved in
OL,17,Fthis and apologises to both the
OL,18,Fcomplainant and the court. His plan,
OL,19,Fwhen released, is to go and live in
OL,20,FPlymouth with his brother."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/13
